{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Earth Day didn't knock gently. It kicked the door wide open. In 1970, oil‑soaked beaches, burning rivers and toxic air mobilised millions into street protests. When looking away was no longer an option, conservation was forced onto political agendas, sparking landmark environmental laws and flipping planet‑care from fringe concern to global priority. Every April 22, over 190 countries pause, reflect and reassess.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_EN-CA4441646278_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_EN-CA4441646278_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The power of protest","Title":"Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve in Tartu County, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/58.466962,26.199884/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=58.466962,26.199884;S9;Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve, Tartu County, Estonia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Earth+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260422_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia"},"Ssd":"20260422","Name":"TartuEstonia","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"4441646278","FullDateString":"Apr. 22, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring arrives with a small, spiky ambassador: the European hedgehog, spotted here in France. Part cuddle, part survival gear, this tiny forager is mostly nocturnal and usually solitary, guided mainly by smell and sound. Its job description is simple: roam, sniff through leaf litter and vacuum up invertebrates like worms, beetles, slugs and caterpillars—the kind of snacks that keep ecosystems running and gardeners smiling. When danger shows up, it doesn't negotiate or flee. It curls into a tight ball and lets its spines do the talking.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_EN-CA4215490891_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_EN-CA4215490891_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spring's prickly patrol","Title":"European hedgehog, France","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Its 5,000-7,000 spines are stiff, hollow hairs made of keratin, not true quills like a porcupine's.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=European+hedgehog&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260421_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog"},"Ssd":"20260421","Name":"SpringHedgehog","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"4215490891","FullDateString":"Apr. 21, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Have you ever enjoyed a plate of pancakes drizzled with maple syrup? That sweet pour starts its journey on a maple tree, following a very particular rhythm in nature. In late winter, sugar maple trees are tapped when days rise above freezing and nights drop below—this freeze–thaw cycle pushes sap through the tree. The clear sap is collected, then boiled down for hours—about 40 litres to make just 1 litre of syrup. The season is brief, often lasting only a few weeks between February and April, so timing matters. Traditional buckets still exist, though many producers now use vacuum tubing to improve efficiency.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MapleExtraction_EN-CA4012556624_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MapleExtraction_EN-CA4012556624_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Canada's liquid gold","Title":"Buckets on maple trees collecting sap for maple syrup","Copyright":"© capecodphoto/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The Great Canadian Maple Syrup Heist (2011–2012) saw nearly 3,000 tonnes of maple syrup stolen over several months from a Quebec storage facility.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260420_MapleExtraction\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Maple+syrup&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260420_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260420_MapleExtraction"},"Ssd":"20260420","Name":"MapleExtraction","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"4012556624","FullDateString":"Apr. 20, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"From above, Brazil's Mirror Beach looks like a watercolour you can walk into. Pale cliffs, reefs stitched into the shoreline and a mosaic of tide pools that, at low tide, reflect the sky and clouds so clearly that the beach earns its name. Tucked into Bahia, a north-eastern state on the Atlantic coast, it sits between small fishing villages in the city of Porto Seguro. Access follows dirt roads and short trails—a natural crowd-control system that keeps the vibe intimate. For years, it stayed off the map, known only through word of mouth, until the 1990s brought it onto travellers' radars.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TranBA_EN-CA3645190031_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TranBA_EN-CA3645190031_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The tide's passing signature","Title":"Mirror Beach, Porto Seguro, Bahia, Brazil","Copyright":"© Marcelo Nacinovic/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-16.729899,-39.126587/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-16.729899,-39.126587;S9;Mirror Beach, Porto Seguro, Bahia, Brazil&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260419_TranBA\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bahia+Brazil&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260419_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260419_TranBA"},"Ssd":"20260419","Name":"TranBA","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"3645190031","FullDateString":"Apr. 19, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, on World Heritage Day, attention turns to places that tell humanity's shared story—protected for their exceptional cultural or natural value. One of them rises from volcanic stone on Easter Island, Chile. At Rano Raraku, the slopes of an extinct volcano became the workshop where nearly all of the island's famous moai were carved. The image captures this remarkable quarry, where half-finished figures emerge from the rock, frozen mid-creation.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MaoiStatues_EN-CA3351921457_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MaoiStatues_EN-CA3351921457_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"The silence of unfinished giants","Title":"Moai statue quarry, Rano Raraku, Easter Island, Chile","Copyright":"© Gavin Hellier/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-27.127001,-109.292099/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-27.127001,-109.292099;S9;Rano Raraku, Easter Island, Chile&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260418_MaoiStatues\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Heritage+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260418_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260418_MaoiStatues"},"Ssd":"20260418","Name":"MaoiStatues","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"3351921457","FullDateString":"Apr. 18, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"On April 17, International Bat Appreciation Day flips its cape to the planet's night shift: bats. With more than 1,400 species on every continent except Antarctica, these winged mammals keep ecosystems balanced. They've been on Earth for over 50 million years, and only three species are true vampires. Found only in the Americas, these bats feed on blood, while the rest survive on insects, fruit, nectar or pollen. In Canada, bats such as the little brown bat and the big brown bat play a key role in controlling insect populations, consuming vast numbers of mosquitoes and agricultural pests each night, supporting both forests and farmlands.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_EN-CA2731028083_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_EN-CA2731028083_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bat signal: ON","Title":"Grey-headed flying fox carrying her pup, Yarra Bend Park, Australia","Copyright":"© Doug Gimesy/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-37.798065,145.012222/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-37.798065,145.012222;S9;Yarra Bend Park, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bats&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260417_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom"},"Ssd":"20260417","Name":"FlyingFoxMom","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"2731028083","FullDateString":"Apr. 17, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What makes a lupine so eye-catching? Start with the shape: tall spires packed with pea-like flowers, often in blues, purples, pinks and whites. Add finely divided leaves and a knack for improving soil by fixing nitrogen, and you've got a plant that's both hardy and useful. Lupines thrive in cool climates, which explains why they spread so easily across parts of Atlantic Canada.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Wildflowerbloom_EN-CA6661555631_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Wildflowerbloom_EN-CA6661555631_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Be a wildflower","Title":"Blooming lupines in Newfoundland","Copyright":"© Nature, Parks/Outdoor/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/48.54167,-56.125/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=48.54167,-56.125;S9;Newfoundland&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260416_Wildflowerbloom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lupinus&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260416_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260416_Wildflowerbloom"},"Ssd":"20260416","Name":"Wildflowerbloom","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6661555631","FullDateString":"Apr. 16, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ships leaving Lisbon once passed a small stone tower before meeting the wide Atlantic. That tower, standing on the bank of the Tagus River, served as both a guardian and a farewell. Say hello to Belém Tower—a fortress that watched Portugal sail into the Age of Exploration.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_EN-CA6523750356_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_EN-CA6523750356_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"History anchored in stone","Title":"Belém Tower on the bank of the Tagus River, Lisbon, Portugal","Copyright":"© f9photos/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.69165,-9.215943/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.69165,-9.215943;S9;Belém Tower, Lisbon, Portugal&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Belem+Tower&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260429_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank"},"Ssd":"20260429","Name":"BelemTowerBank","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6523750356","FullDateString":"Apr. 29, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The spectacled bear, also known as the Andean bear, is the only South American bear of the Ursidae family. Inhabiting the northern and central Andes Mountains, it dwells primarily in forested areas and feeds mainly on shoots and fruit. Pale markings around the eyes often resemble eyeglasses, or 'spectacles,' giving the species its distinctive name.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-CA5387573161_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-CA5387573161_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spectacles in the wild","Title":"Spectacled bear resting in tree, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Each spectacled bear has unique facial markings, which scientists use to identify and track individuals in the wild.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Spectacled+bear&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260428_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear"},"Ssd":"20260428","Name":"AndeanBear","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5387573161","FullDateString":"Apr. 28, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Designed by architect Giuseppe Mengoni and completed in 1877, the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II in Milan, Italy, is one of the world's oldest and most famous shopping arcades. Located between Piazza del Duomo and Piazza della Scala, it features a stunning glass-and-iron roof and an elegant, octagonal layout. Affectionately known as 'Milan's living room,' the Galleria is home to high-end boutiques, historic cafés such as Caffè Biffi and Camparino in Galleria, and renowned restaurants.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-CA9394952547_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-CA9394952547_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Glass with class","Title":"The glass dome of Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy","Copyright":"© PhillipMinnis/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/45.466179,9.18992/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=45.466179,9.18992;S9;Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galleria+Vittorio+Emanuele+II+Milan+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260427_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria"},"Ssd":"20260427","Name":"MilanGalleria","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"9394952547","FullDateString":"Apr. 27, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring brings apple trees to life with clouds of soft pink blossoms. Their delicate petals brighten orchards and hillsides, standing out against clear blue skies as the season shifts from winter toward warmer days. These blooms attract pollinators such as bees and butterflies, helping fruit trees produce the apples that will grow later in the year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-CA6292160620_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-CA6292160620_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bloom boom","Title":"Pink apple blossoms, Avila Beach, California, United States","Copyright":"© Mimi Ditchie Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/35.177404,-120.733528/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=35.177404,-120.733528;S9;Avila Beach, California, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Apple+tree&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260426_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260426","Name":"AppleBlossoms","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6292160620","FullDateString":"Apr. 26, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Penguins usually bring Antarctica to mind, but these endearing flightless seabirds don't always follow the ice. On World Penguin Day, the Galápagos penguins pictured here offer a vivid counterpoint. Found only in the Galápagos Islands—a volcanic archipelago about 966 kilometres off Ecuador's coast—this species lives farther north than any other penguin. Cool, nutrient‑rich ocean currents make this equatorial habitat possible by supplying food and keeping surrounding waters within survivable temperatures. Compact and agile, these birds spend much of the day in the water to stay cool.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_EN-CA5860211884_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_EN-CA5860211884_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Breaking the penguin rules","Title":"Galápagos penguins swimming, Galápagos Islands, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Henley Spiers/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-0.859397,-91.215904/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-0.859397,-91.215904;S9;Galápagos Islands, Ecuador&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Penguin+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260425_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins"},"Ssd":"20260425","Name":"GalapagosPenguins","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5860211884","FullDateString":"Apr. 25, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Arbor Day celebrates the quiet power of trees—the way they steady ecosystems, shelter wildlife, cool cities and shape the environments we rely on every day. Observed in the United States on the last Friday in April, the day encourages communities there—and in many other countries, where dates vary with the growing season—to plant, protect and care for forests of every kind.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_EN-CA5488126378_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_EN-CA5488126378_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A tribute to trees","Title":"Forest hammock of slash pine and saw palmetto, Everglades National Park, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Mary Liz Austin/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/25.400611,-80.658833/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=25.400611,-80.658833;S9;Everglades National Park, Florida, USA&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Arbor+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260424_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine"},"Ssd":"20260424","Name":"SlashPine","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5488126378","FullDateString":"Apr. 24, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each April 23, the curtain rises on the life and legacy of William Shakespeare, a playwright whose words still command the world's literary stage. Shakespeare Day commemorates the anniversary of his death in 1616 and the traditionally accepted date of his birth in 1564—a symbolic pairing that honours a writer whose works reshaped English literature. From the psychological depths of 'Hamlet' to the enduring romance of 'Romeo and Juliet,' his language continues to echo through classrooms, theatres and everyday speech. His plays have been performed in numerous languages worldwide.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HathawayCottage_EN-CA5163724238_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HathawayCottage_EN-CA5163724238_192